	&nbsp;
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage90"></A>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 30PT;COLOR:#0563C1;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<A HREF="#SIEN-20151231X10K_HTM_TOC">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#0563C1;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Table of Contents
</FONT>
</A>
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	In connection with the Original Term Loan Agreement and the Amended Term Loan Agreement, the Company issued to Oxford (i)&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	seven
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	-year warrants in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Jan
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	uary
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2013 to purchase shares of the Company&#x2019;s common stock with a value equal to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	3.0%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	of the tranche A,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	B
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	C
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	term loans amounts and (ii)&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	seven
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	-year warrants in June 2014 to purchase shares of the Company&#x2019;s common stock with a value equal to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2.5%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	of the tranche&nbsp;D term loan amount.&nbsp;&nbsp;The warrants have an exercise price per share of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$14.671
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	On October&nbsp;27, 2015, Oxford issued a notice to Sientra indicating that, in connection with the recent events involving Silimed and the Company, certain events of default have occurred and continue to exist under the Amended Term Loan Agreement. On October&nbsp;28, 2015, Sientra repaid all principal, interest, other amounts and obligations owed to Oxford under the term loans for a total of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$24
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	,539
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, following which the Company has
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	no
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	outstanding debt obligations.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT 36PT;TEXT-INDENT: -36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	(5) Goodwill
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	The Company evaluates goodwill for impairment at least annually on October 1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-SIZE:5PT;TOP:-4PT;POSITION:RELATIVE;LINE-HEIGHT:100%">
	st
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	and whenever circumstances suggest that goodwill may be impaired.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #FFFFFF;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	On September 24, 2015,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	the Company
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	experienced a significant decline in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	its
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	common stock price, which was sustained through September 30, 2015. The significant decline in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	the Company&#x2019;s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	common stock price for a sustained period, along with the impact from regulatory inquiries related to medical devices manufactured by Silimed,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	the Company&#x2019;s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	contract manufacturer, were identified as potential indicators of impairment&nbsp;of goodwill and other intangibles. As a result,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	the Company was
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	required to assess whether or not an impairment of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	its
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	goodwill had occurred as of Septembe
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	r
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	30, 2015.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	The Company
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	assessed the impact of the recent downward volatility in the Company's common stock price and concluded that the sustained decline constituted a triggering event requiring an interim goodwill impairment test.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	The Company
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	conducted the first step of the goodwill impairment test described above for
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	its
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	single reporting unit as of September 30, 2015. The fair value of the reporting unit exceeded its carrying value as of September 30, 2015 by
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	24.7%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, and therefore goodwill was determined to not be impaired as of September 30, 2015.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	As a result of the actions taken by
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	the Brazilian regulatory agency ANVISA
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	on October 2, 2015, and the Company
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	voluntarily placing a hold on the sale of all Sientra devices manufactured by Silimed
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	on October 9, 2015, the Company experienced a significant decline in its common stock price, which was sustained through December 31, 2015. The significant decline in the Company&#x2019;s common stock price for a sustained period, along with the impact from recent regulatory inquiries related to medical devices manufactured by Silimed, the Company&#x2019;s contract manufacturer, were identified as potential indicators of impairment&nbsp;of goodw
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	ill and the Company
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	concluded that the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	se events
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	constituted a triggering event requiring a goodwill impairment test. The Company conducted a step one analysis which consists of a comparison of the fair value of the Company as a single reporting unit using a market approach against its carrying amount, including goodwill.&nbsp;&nbsp;As a result of the step one analysis, it was determined that the carrying value exceeded its fair value; therefore the Company proceeded to step two of the goodwill impairment analysis. For step two, the Company compared the implied fair value of goodwill with the carrying amount of goodwill and based on the analysis, there was no implied goodwill; therefore the Company recorded a goodwill impairment charge of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$14,278
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	for the quarter ended December 31, 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 12PT 36PT;TEXT-INDENT: -36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">

<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	89
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">

	(6

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">

	&nbsp;&#x2014;
</FONT>
</P>

</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM" STYLE="WIDTH:02.56%;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-LEFT:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:2PT DOUBLE #000000 ;BORDER-RIGHT:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;PADDING:0PT;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM" STYLE="WIDTH:14.84%;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-LEFT:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:2PT DOUBLE #000000 ;BORDER-RIGHT:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;PADDING:0PT;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 3PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:RIGHT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

</EFX_UNIDENTIFIED_TABLE>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	The Company has established a full valuation allowance against its
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	net
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	deferred tax assets due to the uncertainty
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	surrounding realization of such assets.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	As of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	December&nbsp;31, 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, the Company had net operating loss carryforwards of approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$137,832
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$120,056
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	available to reduce future taxable income, if any, for federal and state income tax purposes, respectively. The federal net operating loss carryforward begins expiring in 2027, and the state net operating loss carryforward
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	begin expiring in 2017.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	It is possible that
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	the Company
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	will not generate taxable income in time to use these NOLs before their expiration. In addition, under Section 382 of the Internal Revenue
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Code of 1986, as amended, or the Code, if a corporation
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	undergoes an &#x201C;ownership change
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#x201D;, t
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	he corporation's ability to use its pre-change NOL carryforwards and other pre-change tax attributes to offset its post-change income may be limited.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	In general, an &#x201C;ownership change&#x201D; occurs if there is a cumulative change in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	a loss corporation&#x2019;s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	ownership by 5% shareholders that exceeds 50 percentage points over a rolling three-year period.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	The Company has
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	not performed a detailed analysis to determine whether an ownership change under Section 382 of the Code has previously occurred. As a result, if
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	the Company
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	earn
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	net taxable income,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	its
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	ability to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	use
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	their
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	pre-change
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	net operating loss carryforwards to offset U.S. federal taxable income may become subject to limitations, which could potentially result in increased future tax liability
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	to the Company
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	. Until such analysis is completed,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	the Company
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	cannot be sure that the full amount of the existing fede
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	ral NOLs will be available to them, even if
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	taxable income
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	is generated
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	before their expiration.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	As of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	December&nbsp;31, 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, the Company had research and development credit carryforwards of approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$1,804
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$1,762
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	available to reduce future taxable income, if any, for federal and California state income tax purposes,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	r
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	espectively. The federal credit carryforwards begin expiring in 2027 and the state credits carryforward indefinitely.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	At
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	December&nbsp;31, 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, the Company had unrecognized tax benefits of approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$732
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	associated with the research and development
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	credits. The Company does not anticipate that total unrecognized net tax benefits will significantly change over the next twelve months.
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	It is the Company&#x2019;s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	policy to include penalties and interest expense related to income taxes as a component of other expense and interest expense, respectively, as necessary. There was
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	no
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	interest expense or penalties related to unrecognized tax benefits recorded through
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	December&nbsp;31, 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	.
</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	The Company files&nbsp;U.S. federal and state income tax returns
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	in jurisdictions with varying statute of limitations. The years that may be subject to examination will vary by jurisdicti
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	on. The Company&#x2019;s tax years 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	to 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	will remain open for examination by the federal and state tax authorities.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT 36PT;TEXT-INDENT: -36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	(
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">

</FONT>

<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;;">

<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:10PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	Authorized Stock

</TD>

</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	The
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Company&#x2019;s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Amended and Restated Certificate of Incorporation, effective upon the completion of the IPO, authorizes the Company to issue
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	210,000,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	shares of common and preferred stock, consisting of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	200,000,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	shares of common stock with
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$0.01
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	par value and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	10,000,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	shares of preferred stock with
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$0.01
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	par value. As of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	December&nbsp;31, 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, the Company has
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	no
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	preferred stock issued or
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	outstanding
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 1PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:1PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<TABLE STYLE="WIDTH:100%;" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0">
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:0PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:0PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 23.00PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;;">
	(b)
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:13PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:13PT;WIDTH:13PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:10PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	Stock Options
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	In April 2007,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Company adopted the 2007 Equity Incentive Plan, or 2007 Plan. The 2007 Plan provides for the granting of stock options to employees, directors and consultants of the Company. Options granted under the 2007 Plan may either be incentive stock options or nonstatutory stock options. Incentive stock options, or ISO
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	s,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	may be granted only to Company employees.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Nonstatutory stock options, or NSO
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	s,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	may be granted to all eligible recipients. A total of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	1,690,448
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	shares of the Company&#x2019;s common stock were reserved for issuance for the 2007 Plan.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	As of December 31, 2015, pursuant to the 2007 Plan, there were
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	1,605,537
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	shares of common stock reserved and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	no
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	shares of common stock available for future grants.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	The Company&#x2019;s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	board of directors adopted
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2014 Equity Incentive Plan, or 2014 Plan, in July 2014, and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	stockholders approved the 2014 Plan in October 2014. The 2014 Plan became effective upon completion of the IPO, at which time the Company ceased making awards under the 2007 Plan. Under the 2014 Plan, the Company may issue ISO, NSOs, stock appreciation rights, restricted stock awards, restricted stock unit awards and other forms of stock awards, or collectively, stock awards, all of which may be granted to employees, including officers, non-employee directors and consultants of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	the Company
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	their
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	affiliates. ISOs may be granted only to employees.&nbsp;&nbsp;A total of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	1,027,500
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	shares of common stock were initially reserved for issuance under the 2014 Plan, subject to certain annual increases.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Options under the 2007 Plan and the 2014 Plan
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	may
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	be granted for periods of up to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	ten
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	years as determined by
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	the Company&#x2019;s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	board of directors, provided, however, that (i)&nbsp;the exercise price of an ISO shall not be less than
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	100%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	of the estimated fair value of the shares on the date of grant, and (ii)&nbsp;the exercise price of an ISO granted to a more than
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	10%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	shareholder shall not be less than
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	110%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	of the estimated fair value of the shares on the date of grant. An NSO has no such exercise price limitations. The options generally vest with
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	25%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	of the grant vesting on the first anniversary and the balance vesting monthly on a straight-lined basis over the requisite service period of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	three
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	additional years for the award.&nbsp;&nbsp;Additionally, options have been granted to certain key executives which vest upon achievement of performance conditions based on
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	performance targets as defined by the board of directors, which have included
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	net sales targets
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	and defined corporate objectives
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	over the performance period
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	with possible payouts ranging from
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	0%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	100%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	of the target award
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Compensation expense is recognized on a straight-lined basis over the vesting term of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	one
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	year based upon the probable
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>

	$342

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, respectively. Tax benefits arising from the disposition of certain shares issued upon exercise of stock options within
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	two
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	years of the date of grant or within
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	one
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	year of the date of exercise by the option holder, or Disqualifying Dispositions, provide the Company with a tax deduction equal to the difference between the exercise price and the fair market value of the stock on the date of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	exercise. When realized, those excess windfall tax benefits are credited to additional paid-in capital. As of December&nbsp;31, 2015 there
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	was
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$4,733
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	total unrecognized compensation cost related to stock options
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	granted under the plans
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	The costs are expected to be recognized over a weighted
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	average period of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2.95
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	years.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	The expense is recorded within the operating expense
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	components
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	in the statement of operations based on the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	employees receiving the awards.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	The aggregate intrinsic value of stock options is
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	calculated as the difference between the exercise price of the stock options and the fair value of the Company&#x2019;s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	common stock for those stock options that had exercise prices lower than the fair value of the Company&#x2019;s common stock. The aggregate intrinsic value of stock options exercised was
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$597
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$176
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	during the years ended
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	December&nbsp;31, 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2014
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2013
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	respectively
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;PADDING:0PT 36PT 0PT 0PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:1PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	The expected term of employee stock options, risk
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#8209;free interest rate and volatility represents the weighted average, based on grant date period, which the stock options are expected to remain outstanding. The Company utilized the simplified method to estimate the expected term of the options pursuant to ASC Subtopic 718
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#8209;10 for all option grants to employees. The expected volatility is based upon historical volatilities of an index of a peer group because it is not practicable to make a reasonable estimate of the Company&#x2019;s volatility. The risk
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#8209;free interest rate is based on the U.S. Treasury yield curve in effect at the time of the grant for periods corresponding with the expected term of the option. The dividend yield assumption is based on the Company&#x2019;s history and expectation of dividend payouts. The Company has never declared or paid any cash dividends on its common stock, and the Company does not anticipate paying any cash dividends in the foreseeable future.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	As stock
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#8209;based compensation expense recognized in the Company&#x2019;s statement of operations is based on awards ultimately expected to vest, the amount has been reduced for estimated forfeitures. Forfeitures were estimated based on the Company&#x2019;s historical experience and future expectations.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	For purposes of financial accounting for stock
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#8209;based compensation, the Company has determined the fair values of its options based in part on the work of a third
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#8209;party valuation specialist. The determination of stock
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#8209;based compensation is inherently uncertain and subjective and involves the application of valuation models and assumptions requiring the use
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT;">

<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:10PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	Employee Stock Purchase Plan
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	The Company&#x2019;s board of directors adopted the 2014 Employee Stock Purchase Plan, or ESPP, in July 2014, and the stockholders approved the ESPP in October 2014. The ESPP allows eligible employees to purchase shares of the Company&#x2019;s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	common stock at a discount through payroll deductions of up to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	15%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	of their eligible compensation, subject to any plan limitations. The ESPP provides offering periods not to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	exceed
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	27
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	months
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, and each offering period will include purchase periods, which will be the approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	six
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	-month period commencing with one exercise date and ending with the next exercise date, except that the first offering period commenced on the first trading day following the effective date of the Company's registration statement.&nbsp;&nbsp;Employees are able to purchase shares at
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	85%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	of the lower of the fair market value of the Company&#x2019;s common stock on the first trading day of the offering period or on the exercise date.&nbsp;&nbsp;The number of shares available for sale under the 2014 Employee Stock Purchase Plan will be
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	increased annually on the first day of each fiscal year, equal to the lesser of i)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	1%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	of the total outstanding shares of the Company&#x2019;s common stock as of the last day of the immediately preceding fiscal year; ii)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	3,000,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	shares of common stock, or iii) such lesser amount as determined by the board of directors.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	As of December 31, 2015, the number of shares of common stock reserved for issuance under the ESPP was
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	404,629
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	During the year ended
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	December&nbsp;31, 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, employees purchased
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	44,250
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	shares under the 2014 ESPP at a weighted average exercise price of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$12.75
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	per share. As of December 31, 2015, the number of shares of common stock available for future issuance under the ESPP was
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	360,379
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	. Stock
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	-based compensation related to the ESPP for the years ended December 31, 2015 and 2014 was
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$375
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$34
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, respectively.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>

<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">

<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:0PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:0PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 23.00PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;;">
	(a)
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:13PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:13PT;WIDTH:13PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:10PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	Operating Lease Commitment
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	In August 2013, the Company entered into a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	four
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	month warehouse lease in Santa Barbara, California, commencing on September 1, 2013. This operating lease is used for additional general office, warehouse, and research and development. This lease has been renewed until January 2019.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	In March 2014, the Company entered into a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	68
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	month lease agreement in Santa Barbara, California. The operating lease is for general office use only and commenced on July 1, 2014.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
</FONT>

	The terms of the facility lease provide for rental payments on a graduated scale. The Company recognizes rent expense on a straight-line basis over the lease term. Rent expense for the years ended

</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	On November&nbsp;12, 2015, the Company entered into the following Separation and Consulting Agreements:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

</FONT>

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$871
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	twelve
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	with the completion of the fiscal year prior to the separation date, and (ii)&nbsp;up to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	twelve
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	(12) months of company-paid health insurance premiums to continue his coverage. As a result of this Separation Agreement, the Company incurred
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$871
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	in termination benefits which was recorded during the year ended December 31, 2015.

	Further, o

	n February 16, 2

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">

	thirty
</FONT>

	$43
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	per month. As a result of the terms and conditions of this Consulting Agreement, the Company accrued for all consulting services to be rendered of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$586
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	which was recorded during the year ended December 31, 2015.

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">

	$113
</FONT>

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	In 2012, the Company filed a claim with the Hartford Insurance Company, or Hartford for reimbursement of legal costs incurred in connection with litigation with a competitor that was resolved in 2013. The Company held a D&amp;O insurance policy with Hartford, and the Company and Hartford settled the matter in May 2014. The Company received settlement payments from Hartford and recovery of costs associated with the litigation of

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	On September&nbsp;25, 2015, a lawsuit styled as a class action of the Company&#x2019;s stockholders was filed in the United States District Court for the Central District of California. The lawsuit names the Company and certain of its officers as defendants and alleges violations of Sections 10(b)&nbsp;and 20(a)&nbsp;of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934, as amended, or the

</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:24PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	94
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">

	&nbsp;

<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 30PT;COLOR:#0563C1;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<A HREF="#SIEN-20151231X10K_HTM_TOC">

	Table of Contents
</FONT>
</A>

<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Exchange Act, in connection with allegedly false and misleading statements concerning the Company&#x2019;s business, operations, and prospects.&nbsp; The plaintiff seeks damages and an award of reasonable costs and expenses, including attorneys&#x2019; fees.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	On November 24, 2015,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	three
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	stockholders (or groups of stockholders) filed
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	motions to appoint lead plainti
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	ff(s) and to approve their selection on lead counsel.&nbsp; On December 10, 2015, the court entered an order appointing lead plaintiffs and approving their se
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	lection of lead counsel.&nbsp; On February 19, 2016, lead plaintiffs filed their consolidated amended complaint.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	On October&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	28
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, November 5,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	and November 19,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2015,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	three
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	lawsuits styled as class actions of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	the Company&#x2019;s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	stockholders were filed in the Superior Court of California for the County of San Mateo. The lawsuits name
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	the Company
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, certain of its officers and directors, and the underwriters associated with
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	the Company&#x2019;s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	follow-on public offering that closed on September&nbsp;23, 2015 as defendants. The lawsuits allege violations of Sections 11, 12(a)(2), and 15 of the Securities Act in connection with allegedly false and misleading statements in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	the Company&#x2019;s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	offering documents associated with the follow-on offering concerning
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	its
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	business, operations, and prospects. The plaintiffs seek damages and an award of reasonable costs and expenses, including attorneys&#x2019; fees.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	On December 4, 2015, defendants removed all
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	three
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	lawsuits to the United States District Court for the Northern District of California.&nbsp; On December 15 and December 16, 2015, plaintiffs filed motions to remand the lawsuits back to San Mateo Superior Court
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, or
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Motions to Remand.&nbsp; On January 19, 2016, defendants filed their opposition to the Motions to Remand, and plaintiffs filed their reply in support of the Motions to Remand on January 26, 2016.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	It is possible that additional suits will be filed, or allegations made by stockholders, with respect to these same or other matters and also naming the Company and/or its officers and directors as defendants.&nbsp;The Company believes it has meritorious defenses and intends to defend these lawsuits vigorously.&nbsp; Due to the early stage of these proceedings,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	the Company is not able to predict or reasonably estimate the ultimate outcome or possible losses relating to these claims.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	(9
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	) Subsequent Events
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	(a)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:10PT;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;PADDING:0PT 36PT 0PT 0PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Resumption of Sales
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:10PT;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;PADDING:0PT 36PT 0PT 0PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	On March 1, 2016, after
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	the completion of extensive independent, third-party testing and analyses of our Breast Products in the U.S.,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	we lifted
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	the temporary hold on
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	the sale of our devices manufactured by Silimed.&nbsp;&nbsp;We also sent a letter to our Plastic Surgeons informing them of the Company&#x2019;s market re-entry plans. The conclusive results of our testing indicate no anticipated significant safety concerns with the use of our products, including our breast implants, consistent with their approval status since 2012.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	(b)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;PADDING:0PT 36PT 0PT 0PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	c
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	qu
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	i
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	sition of bioCorneum
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	On March 9, 2016, pursuant to the Asset Purchase Agreement, or the Purchase Agreement, by and among the Company, Enaltus, LLC, and HealthEdge Investment Fund, L.P, we acquired certain assets of bioCorneum, an advanced silicone gel scar management therapy product for the purchase price of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$7,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	in cash.&nbsp; The assets
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	acquired consist of inventory, intellectual p
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	roperty, specified contracts and the associated assumed liabilities.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:10PT;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;PADDING:0PT 36PT 0PT 0PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	We expect to account for the transaction as a business combination and are in the process of determining the allocation of the purchase price to acquired assets and assumed liabilities.&nbsp;A determination of the acquisition-date fair values of the assets acquired and the liabilities assumed is pending the completion of an independent appraisal and other evaluations and therefore further disclosures have not been made
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

<P STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;PUNCTUATION-WRAP:HANGING;VERTICAL-ALIGN:BASELINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">

	(e)

	Post-Service Option Exercise Period.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">

	&nbsp;

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	of this Agreement, and that each party shall be entitled to an injunction both preliminary and final, and any other appropriate equitable relief to enforce her or its rights set forth in these Sections.&nbsp;&nbsp;Such remedies shall be cumulative and non-exclusive, being in addition to any and all other remedies either party may have.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;;;PADDING:0PT 20PT 0PT 0PT;">
	10.

</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 100%;TEXT-INDENT:36PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;PUNCTUATION-WRAP:HANGING;VERTICAL-ALIGN:BASELINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;PUNCTUATION-WRAP:HANGING;VERTICAL-ALIGN:BASELINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-SIZE:12PT;;;PADDING:0PT 22PT 0PT 0PT;">
	(a)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	General Release.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	In exchange for the consideration provided to you under this Agreement to which you would not otherwise be entitled, including but not limited to the Separation Benefits, you hereby generally and completely release the Company and its current and former directors, officers, employees, shareholders, partners, agents, attorneys, predecessors, successors, parent and subsidiary entities, insurers, affiliates, investors and assigns (collectively, the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#x201C;Released Parties&#x201D;) of and from any and all claims, liabilities and obligations, both known and known, that arise out of or are in any way related to events, acts, conduct, or omissions occurring prior to or on the date you sign this Agreement (collectively, the &#x201C;Released Claims&#x201D;)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<P STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;PUNCTUATION-WRAP:HANGING;VERTICAL-ALIGN:BASELINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;PUNCTUATION-WRAP:HANGING;VERTICAL-ALIGN:BASELINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-SIZE:12PT;;;PADDING:0PT 22PT 0PT 0PT;">
	(b)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	Scope of Release.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The Released Claims include, but are not limited to: (i) all claims arising out of or in any way related to your employment with the Company, the Employment Agreement, or the termination of your employment: (ii) all claims related to your compensation or benefits from the Company, including salary, bonuses, commissions, vacation pay, expense reimbursements, severance pay, fringe benefits, stock, stock options, or any other ownership interests in the Company: (iii) all claims for breach of contract, wrongful termination, and breach of the implied covenant of good faith and fair dealing; (iv) all tort claims, including claims for fraud, defamation, emotional distress, wrongful termination, and discharge in violation of public policy; and (v) all federal, state, and local statutory claims, including claims for discrimination, harassment, retaliation, attorneys&#x2019; fees, or other claims arising under the federal Civil Rights Act of 1964 (as amended), the federal Americans with Disabilities Act of 1990, the Age Discrimination in Employment Act
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	(&#x201C;ADEA&#x201D;), the federal Family and Medical Leave Act (as amended) (&#x201C;FMLA&#x201D;), the California Family Rights Act (&#x201C;CFRA&#x201D;), the California Labor Code (as amended), the California Unruh Act, and the California Fair Emp
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	loyment and Housing Act (as amended).
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

	23.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	Section 409A.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;It is intended that all of the benefits and payments payable under this Agreement satisfy, to the greatest extent possible, an exemption from Section 409A of the Internal Revenue Code of 1986, as amended
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	(&#x201C;Section 409A&#x201D;),
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	and this Agreement will be construed to the greatest extent possible as consistent with those exemptions, and to the extent not so exempt, this Agreement (and any definitions hereunder) will be construed to the greatest extent possible in a manner that complies with Section 409A. For purposes of Section 409A, your right to receive any installment payments under this Agreement (whether severance payments, reimbursements or otherwise) shall be treated as a right to receive a series of separate payments and, accordingly, each installment payment hereunder shall at all times be considered a separate and distinct payment. Notwithstanding any provision to the contrary in this Agreement, if you are deemed by the Company at the time of your separation from service to be a &#x201C;specified employee&#x201D; for purposes of Section 409A, and if any of the payments upon separation from service set forth herein and/or under any other agreement with the Company are deemed to be &#x201C;deferred compensation&#x201D;, then to the extent delayed commencement of any portion of such payments is required in order to avoid a prohibited distribution under Section 409A and the related adverse taxation under Section 409A, such payments shall not be provided to you prior to the earliest of (i) the expiration of the six-month period measured from the date of your separation from service, (ii) the date of your death or (iii) such earlier date as permitted under Section 409A without the imposition of adverse taxation. If the release revocation period spans two calendar years, payments will commence in the second of those two calendar years to the extent required to comply with Section 409A.
</FONT>
</P>

<A NAME="SIEN-20151231EX10204A230_HTM__REF98825084">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	Eligible Stock Award Recipients.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The only persons eligible to receive grants of Stock Awards under this Plan are individuals who satisfy the standards for inducement grants under
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	NASDAQ
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Marketplace Rule 5635(c)(4) and the related guidance under
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	NASDAQ
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	IM 5635-1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	. A person who previously served as an Employee or Director
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	will
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	not be eligible to receive Stock Awards under the Plan, other than following a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	bona fide
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	period of non-employment. Person
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	eligible
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	to receive grants of Stock Awards under this Plan
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	are referred to in this Plan as &#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Eligible Employees
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#x201D;. These
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Stock Awards must
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	be approved by either a majority of the Company's &#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Independent Directors
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">

	)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	or
</FONT>

	the Company&#x2019;s compensation committee, provided such committee is
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	comp
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	rised
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	solely of Independent Directors
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	(the &#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Independent Compensation Committee
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#x201D;)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	in order to comply with the exemption from the stockholder approval requirement for &#x201C;inducement grants&#x201D; provided under Rule 5635(c)(4) of the NASDAQ Listing Rules.

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Plan, through the granting of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Stock
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Awards, is intended to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	provide
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	(i)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	an inducement material for
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	certain individuals
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	to enter into employment with the Company within the meaning of Rule 5635(c)(4) of the NASDAQ Listing Rules
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	, (ii)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	incentives for such persons to exert maximum efforts for the success of the Company and any Affiliate and (iii) a means by which Eligible Employees may be given an opportunity to benefit from increases in value of the Common Stock through the granting of Stock Awards.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>

	2.

<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;;;PADDING:0PT 22PT 0PT 0PT;">
	(vi)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	To amend the Plan in any respect the Board deems necessary or advisable, including, without limitation, adopting amendments relating to nonqualified deferred compensation under Section 409A
</FONT>

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	of the Code
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	, subject to the limitations, if any, of applicable law.

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	I
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	f required by applicable law
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	or listing requirements
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	, and except as provided in Section&nbsp;9(a) relating to Capitalization Adjustments, the Company will seek stockholder approval of any amendment of the Plan that (A)&nbsp;materially increases the number of shares of Common Stock available for issuance under the Plan, (B)&nbsp;materially expands the class of individuals eligible to receive
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Stock
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Awards under the Plan, (C)&nbsp;materially increases the benefits accruing to Participants under the Plan, (D
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	)&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	materially reduces the price at which shares of Common Stock may be issued or purchased under the Plan, (E)&nbsp;materially extends the term of the Plan, or (F)&nbsp;materially expands the types of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Stock
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Awards available for issuance under the Plan.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Except as
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	otherwise
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	provided in the Plan (including subsection (viii) below) or
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	a Stock Award
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Agreement, no amendment of the Plan will
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	materially
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	impair a Participant&#x2019;s rights under an
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	outstanding Stock Award
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	without
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	the Participant&#x2019;s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	written consent.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>

	the Participant&#x2019;s rights

<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;;;PADDING:0PT 26PT 0PT 0PT;">
	(i)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	General.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The Board may delegate some or all of the administration of the Plan to a Committee or Committees.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	If administration of the Plan is delegated to a Committee, the Committee will have, in connection with the administration of the Plan, the powers theretofore possessed by the Board that have been delegated to the Committee, including the power to delegate to a subcommittee of the Committee any of the administrative powers the Committee is authorized to exercise (and references in this Plan to the Board will thereafter be to the Committee or subcommittee).
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Any delegation of administrative powers will be reflected in resolutions, not inconsistent with the provisions of the Plan, adopted from time to time by the Board or Committee (as applicable).
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The Committee may, at any time, abolish the subcommittee and/or revest in the Committee any powers delegated to the subcommittee.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The Board may retain the authority to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">

</P>

<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 100%;TEXT-INDENT:72PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;;;PADDING:0PT 24PT 0PT 0PT;">
	(ii)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	Rule 16b-3 Compliance.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The Committee may consist
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	solely
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	of two or more Non-Employee Directors, in accordance with Rule 16b-3
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	of the Exchange Act
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	.

<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;;;PADDING:0PT 22PT 0PT 0PT;">
	(a)
</FONT>

<A NAME="SIEN-20151231EX10204A230_HTM__REF38179407">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">

</TD>

<P STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;;;PADDING:0PT 26PT 0PT 0PT;">
	(i)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Subject to Section 9(a) relating to Capitalization Adjustments, the aggregate number of shares of Common Stock that may be issued pursuant to Stock Awards will not exceed
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	180,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	shares
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">

</FONT>

<P STYLE="WIDTH:0PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 100%;TEXT-INDENT:72PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;;;PADDING:0PT 24PT 0PT 0PT;">
	(ii)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	For clarity, the Share Reserve is a limitation on the number of shares of Common Stock that may be issued
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	under
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	to the Plan. A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	s a single share may be subject to grant more than once (
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	e.g.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	, if a share subject to a Stock Award is forfeited, it may be made subject to grant again as provided in Section 3(b) below), the Share Reserve is not a limit on the number of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Stock Awards
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	that can be granted
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>

<TABLE STYLE="WIDTH:100%;" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0">
