<TD STYLE="WIDTH:0PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:0PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 100%;TEXT-INDENT:72PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;;;PADDING:0PT 22PT 0PT 0PT;">
	(iii)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Shares may be issued
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	under the terms of this Plan
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	in connection with a merger or acquisition as permitted by NASDAQ Listing Rule 5635(c), NYSE Listed Company Manual Section 303A.08, AMEX Company Guide Section 711 or other applicable rule, and such issuance will not reduce the number of shares available for issuance under the Plan.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<TABLE STYLE="WIDTH:100%;" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0">
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:0PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:0PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 100%;TEXT-INDENT:36PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;;;PADDING:0PT 22PT 0PT 0PT;">
	(b)
</FONT>
<A NAME="SIEN-20151231EX10204A230_HTM__REF134435282">
</A>
<A NAME="SIEN-20151231EX10204A230_HTM__REF126997548">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	Reversion of Shares to the Share Reserve
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	If a Stock Award or any portion
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	of a Stock Award
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	(i)&nbsp;expires or otherwise terminates without all of the shares covered by
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Stock Award having been issued
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	or (ii)&nbsp;is settled in cash (
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	i.e.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	, the Participant receives cash rather than stock), such expiration, termination or settlement will not reduce (or otherwise offset) the number of shares of Common Stock that
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	are
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	available for issuance under the Plan.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	If any shares of Common Stock issued
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	under
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	a Stock Award are forfeited back to or repurchased by the Company because of the failure to meet a contingency or condition required to vest such shares in the Participant, then the shares that are forfeited or repurchased will revert to and again become available for issuance under the Plan.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Any shares reacquired by the Company in satisfaction of tax withholding obligations on a Stock Award or as consideration for the exercise or purchase price of a Stock Award will again become available for issuance under the Plan.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;;;PADDING:0PT 23PT 0PT 0PT;">
	(c)

	Source of Shares.

<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">

<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:0PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:0PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 100%;TEXT-INDENT:0PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;;;PADDING:0PT 26PT 0PT 0PT;">
	4.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	Eligibility.
</FONT>
</P>

<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<TABLE STYLE="WIDTH:100%;" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0">
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:0PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:0PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 100%;TEXT-INDENT:36PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;;;PADDING:0PT 22PT 0PT 0PT;">
	(a)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	Eligibility
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	for
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	Specific
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	Stock Awards
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Stock Awards
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	may only be granted to persons who are
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Eligible
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Employees described in Section 1(a) of the Plan, where the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Stock Award
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	is an inducement material to the individual&#x2019;s entering into employment with the Company or an Affiliate within the meaning of Rule 5635(c)(4) of the NASDAQ Listing Rules,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	provided however
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	, that
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Stock Awards may not be granted to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Eligible
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Employees who are providing Continuous Service only to any &#x201C;parent&#x201D; of the Company, as such term is defined in Rule&nbsp;405
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	of the Securities Act
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	, unless (i) the stock underlying such Stock Awards is treated as &#x201C;service recipient stock&#x201D; under
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Section 409A of the Code
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	(for example, because the Stock Awards are granted pursuant to a corporate transaction such as a spin off transaction),
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	or
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	(ii) the Company, in consultation with its legal counsel, has determined that such Stock Awards are otherwise exempt from
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	or comply
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	with the distribution requirements of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Section 409A of the Code
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>

<TABLE STYLE="WIDTH:100%;" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0">
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:0PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:0PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 100%;TEXT-INDENT:36PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">

	(b)

<A NAME="SIEN-20151231EX10204A230_HTM__DV_M89">

<A NAME="SIEN-20151231EX10204A230_HTM__REF92447500">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">

	All
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Stock Awards
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	must be granted either by a majority of the Company&#x2019;s independent directors or

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">

<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;;;PADDING:0PT 26PT 0PT 0PT;">
	5.
</FONT>
<A NAME="SIEN-20151231EX10204A230_HTM__REF92447517">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	Provisions Relating to Options.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Each Option will be in such form and will contain such terms and conditions as the Board deems appropriate.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	All Options will be Nonstatutory Stock Options. The provisions of separate Options need not be identical;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	provided, however
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, that each Option Agreement will conform to (through incorporation of provisions hereof by reference in the applicable Option Agreement or otherwise) the substance of each of the following provisions:
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<TABLE STYLE="WIDTH:100%;" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0">
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:0PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:0PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 100%;TEXT-INDENT:36PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;;;PADDING:0PT 22PT 0PT 0PT;">
	(a)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	Term.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	No Option will be exercisable after the expiration of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	10
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	years from the date of its grant or such shorter period specified in the Option Agreement.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>

<TABLE STYLE="WIDTH:100%;" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0">

</P>

<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 100%;TEXT-INDENT:36PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;;;PADDING:0PT 22PT 0PT 0PT;">
	(b)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	Exercise Price.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The exercise or strike price of each Option will be not less than 100% of the Fair Market Value of the Common Stock subject to the Option on the date the Option is granted.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Notwithstanding the foregoing, an Option may be granted with an exercise
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	price lower than 100% of the Fair Market Value of the Common Stock subject to the Option if such Option is granted pursuant to an assumption of or substitution for another option or stock appreciation right pursuant to a Corporate Transaction and in a manner consistent with the provisions of Section 409A of the Code.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;;;PADDING:0PT 22PT 0PT 0PT;">

<P STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;;;PADDING:0PT 22PT 0PT 0PT;">
	(iv)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	by a &#x201C;net exercise&#x201D; arrangement pursuant to which the Company will reduce the number of shares of Common Stock issuable upon exercise by the largest whole number of shares with a Fair Market Value that does not exceed the aggregate exercise price;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	provided, however
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	that the Company will accept a cash or other payment from the Participant to the extent of any remaining balance of the aggregate exercise price not satisfied by such reduction in the number of whole shares to be issued.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Shares of Common Stock will no longer be subject to an Option and will not be exercisable thereafter to the extent that (A) shares issuable upon exercise are
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	used
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	to pay the exercise price pursuant to the &#x201C;net exercise,&#x201D; (B) shares are delivered to the Participant as a result of such exercise, and (C) shares are withheld to satisfy tax withholding obligations;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	or
</FONT>
</P>

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">

<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<TABLE STYLE="WIDTH:100%;" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0">

<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 100%;TEXT-INDENT:72PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;;;PADDING:0PT 26PT 0PT 0PT;">
	(i)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	Restrictions on Transfer.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	An Option will not be transferable except by will or by the laws of descent and distribution (or pursuant to subsections (ii) and (iii) below), and will be exercisable during the lifetime of the Participant only by the Participant.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The Board may permit transfer of the Option in a manner that is not prohibited by applicable tax and securities laws. Except as explicitly provided
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	in the Plan
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	, an Option may not be transferred for consideration.
</FONT>
</P>

<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;;;PADDING:0PT 22PT 0PT 0PT;">
	(iii)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	Beneficiary Designation.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Subject to the approval of the Board or a duly authorized Officer, a Participant may, by delivering written notice to the Company, in a form approved by the Company (or the designated broker), designate a third party who, on the death of the Participant, will thereafter be entitled to exercise the Option and receive the Common Stock or other consideration resulting from such exercise.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	In the absence of such a designation, the executor or administrator of the Participant&#x2019;s estate will be entitled to exercise the Option and receive the Common Stock or other consideration resulting from such exercise. However, the Company may prohibit designation of a beneficiary at any time, including due to any conclusion by the Company that such designation would be inconsistent with the provisions of applicable laws.
</FONT>

	(f)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	Termination of Continuous Service.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Except as otherwise provided in the applicable Option Agreement or other agreement between the Participant and the Company, if a Participant&#x2019;s Continuous Service terminates (other than for Cause and other than upon the Participant&#x2019;s death or Disability), the Participant may exercise his or her Option
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	(to the extent that the Participant was entitled to exercise such Option as of the date of termination of Continuous Service) within the period of time ending on the earlier of (i) the date
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	which occurs ninety (90) days
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	following the termination of the Participant&#x2019;s Continuous Service
</FONT>
<A NAME="SIEN-20151231EX10204A230_HTM__DV_C248">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:LINE-THROUGH;COLOR:#FF0000;DISPLAY:INLINE;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	and (ii) the expiration of the term of the Option as set forth in the Option Agreement.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	If, after termination of Continuous Service, the Participant does not exercise his or her Option within the applicable time frame, the Option will terminate.
</FONT>
</P>

</FONT>

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">

	days or
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	months (that need not be consecutive) equal to the applicable post-termination exercise period after the termination of the Participant&#x2019;s Continuous Service during which the sale of the Common Stock received upon exercise of the Option would not be in violation of the Company&#x2019;s insider trading policy, or (ii) the expiration of the term of the Option as set forth in the applicable Option Agreement.

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Continuous Service terminates as a result of the Participant&#x2019;s death, or (ii) the Participant dies within the period (if any) specified in the Option Agreement for exercisability after the termination of the Participant&#x2019;s Continuous Service for a reason other than death, then the Option may be exercised (to the extent the Participant was entitled to exercise such Option as of the date of death) by the Participant&#x2019;s estate, by a person who acquired the right to exercise the Option by bequest or inheritance or by a person designated to exercise the Option upon the Participant&#x2019;s death, but only within the period ending on the earlier of (i) the date 18 months following the date of death
</FONT>
<A NAME="SIEN-20151231EX10204A230_HTM__DV_C274">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:LINE-THROUGH;COLOR:#FF0000;DISPLAY:INLINE;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;

<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;;;PADDING:0PT 26PT 0PT 0PT;">
	(j)

<A NAME="SIEN-20151231EX10204A230_HTM__DV_M106">
</A>
<A NAME="SIEN-20151231EX10204A230_HTM__DV_M107">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	Termination for Cause.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Except as explicitly provided otherwise in a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Participant&#x2019;s Stock Award Agreement
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	or other individual written agreement between the Company or any Affiliate and the Participant, if a Participant&#x2019;s Continuous Service is terminated for Cause, the Option will terminate upon the date on which the event giving rise to the termination for Cause first occurred, and the Participant will be prohibited from exercising his or her Option from and after the date on which the event giving rise to the termination for Cause first occurred (or, if required by law, the date of termination of Continuous Service).
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	If a Participant&#x2019;s Continuous Service is suspended pending an investigation of the existence of Cause, all of the Participant&#x2019;s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	rights under the Option
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	will also be suspended during the investigation period.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<TABLE STYLE="WIDTH:100%;" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0">
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:0PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:0PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 100%;TEXT-INDENT:36PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;;;PADDING:0PT 23PT 0PT 0PT;">
	(k)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	Non-Exempt Employees
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	If an Option is granted to an Employee who is a non-exempt employee for purposes of the Fair Labor Standards Act of 1938, as amended, the Option will not be first exercisable for any shares of Common Stock until at least 6 months following the date of grant of the Option (although the Option may vest prior to such date). Consistent with the provisions of the Worker Economic Opportunity Act, (i)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	if such non-exempt Employee dies or suffers a Disability, (ii) upon a Corporate Transaction in which such Option is not assumed, continued, or substituted, (iii) upon a Change in Control, or (iv) upon the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	non-exempt Employee
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#x2019;s retirement (as such term may be defined in the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	non-exempt Employee&#x2019;s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Option Agreement in another agreement between the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	non-exempt Employee
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	and the Company, or, if no such definition, in accordance with the Company's then current employment policies and guidelines), the vested portion of any
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Options may be exercised earlier than
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	months following the date of grant.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The foregoing provision is intended to operate so that any income derived by a non-exempt employee in connection with the exercise or vesting of an Option will be exempt from his or her regular rate of pay. To the extent permitted and/or required for compliance with the Worker Economic Opportunity Act to ensure that any income derived by a non-exempt
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	E
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	mployee in connection with the exercise, vesting or issuance of any shares under any other Option will be exempt from
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	such
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	E
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	mployee&#x2019;s regular rate of pay, the provisions of this
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	paragraph
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	will apply to all Options and are hereby incorporated by reference into such Option Agreements.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	Provisions Relating to Restricted Stock Unit Awards.
</FONT>

<A NAME="SIEN-20151231EX10204A230_HTM__DV_M115">
</A>
<A NAME="SIEN-20151231EX10204A230_HTM__REF92447212">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Each Restricted Stock Unit Award Agreement will be in such form and will contain such terms and conditions as the Board deems appropriate.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The terms and conditions of Restricted Stock Unit Award Agreements may change from time to time, and the terms and conditions of separate Restricted Stock Unit Award Agreements need not be identical.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Each Restricted Stock Unit Award
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
</FONT>
</P>

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Agreement will conform to (through incorporation of the provisions hereof by reference in the Agreement or otherwise) the substance of each of the following provisions:
</FONT>

<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<TABLE STYLE="WIDTH:100%;" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0">
<TR>

<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 100%;TEXT-INDENT:36PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;;;PADDING:0PT 22PT 0PT 0PT;">
	(a)
</FONT>
<A NAME="SIEN-20151231EX10204A230_HTM__DV_M116">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	Consideration.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	At the time of grant of a Restricted Stock Unit Award, the Board will determine the consideration, if any, to be paid by the Participant upon delivery of each share of Common Stock subject to the Restricted Stock Unit Award.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The consideration to be paid (if any) by the Participant for each share of Common Stock subject to a Restricted Stock Unit Award may be paid in any form of legal consideration that may be acceptable to the Board
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	in its sole discretion
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	and permissible under applicable law.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	A Restricted Stock Unit Award may be settled by the delivery of shares of Common Stock, their cash equivalent, any combination thereof or in any other form of consideration, as determined by the Board and contained in the Restricted Stock Unit Award Agreement.

</FONT>
<A NAME="SIEN-20151231EX10204A230_HTM__DV_M119">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	Additional Restrictions.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	At the time of the grant of a Restricted Stock Unit Award, the Board, as it deems appropriate, may impose such restrictions or conditions that delay the delivery of the shares of Common Stock (or their cash equivalent) subject to a Restricted Stock Unit Award to a time after the vesting of such Restricted Stock Unit Award.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>

<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 100%;TEXT-INDENT:36PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;;;PADDING:0PT 22PT 0PT 0PT;">
	(e)
</FONT>
<A NAME="SIEN-20151231EX10204A230_HTM__DV_M120">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	Dividend Equivalents.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Dividend equivalents may be credited in respect of shares of Common Stock covered by a Restricted Stock Unit Award, as determined by the Board and contained in the Restricted Stock Unit Award Agreement.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	At the sole discretion of the Board, such dividend equivalents may be converted into additional shares of Common Stock covered by the Restricted Stock Unit Award in such manner as determined by the Board.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Any additional shares covered by the Restricted Stock Unit Award credited by reason of such dividend equivalents will be subject to all of the same terms and conditions of the underlying Restricted Stock Unit Award Agreement to which they relate.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>

	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">

<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;;;PADDING:0PT 26PT 0PT 0PT;">

<A NAME="SIEN-20151231EX10204A230_HTM__DV_M128">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	Covenants of the Company.

<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<TABLE STYLE="WIDTH:100%;" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0">
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:0PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:0PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 100%;TEXT-INDENT:36PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;;;PADDING:0PT 22PT 0PT 0PT;">
	(a)
</FONT>
<A NAME="SIEN-20151231EX10204A230_HTM__REF147744725">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	Availability of Shares.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The Company will keep available at all times the number of shares of Common Stock reasonably required to satisfy then-outstanding
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Stock
</FONT>

A Participant will not be eligible for the grant of

<P STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;;;PADDING:0PT 22PT 0PT 0PT;">
	(e)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	Change in Time Commitment
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	In the event a Participant&#x2019;s regular level of time commitment in the performance of his or her services for the Company and any Affiliates is reduced (for example, and without limitation, if the Participant is an Employee of the Company and the Employee has a change in status from a full-time Employee to a part-time Employee
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	or takes an extended leave of absence
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	) after the date of grant of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	any Stock Award
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	to the Participant, the Board has the ri
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	ght in its sole discretion to (
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	i
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	) make a corresponding reduction in the number of shares
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	or cash amount
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	subject to any portion of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	such Stock Award
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	that is scheduled to vest or become payable after the date of such c
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	hange in time commitment, and (
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	ii
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	) in lieu of or in combination with such a reduction, extend the vesting or payment schedule applicable to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	such Stock Award
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	. In the event of any such reduction, the Participant will have no right with respect to any portion of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	the Stock Award
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	that is so reduced or extended.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<TABLE STYLE="WIDTH:100%;" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0">
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:0PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:0PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 100%;TEXT-INDENT:36PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;;;PADDING:0PT 25PT 0PT 0PT;">
	(f)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	Investment Assurances.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The Company may require a Participant, as a condition of exercising or acquiring Common Stock under any
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Stock
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Award, (i)&nbsp;to give written assurances satisfactory to the Company as to the Participant&#x2019;s knowledge and experience in financial and business matters and/or to employ a purchaser representative reasonably satisfactory to the Company who is knowledgeable and experienced in financial and business matters and that he or she is capable of evaluating, alone or together with the purchaser representative, the merits and risk
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	s of exercising the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Stock
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Award,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	and (ii)&nbsp;to give written assurances satisfactory to the Company stating that the Participant is acquiring Common Stock subject to the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Stock Award
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	for the Participant&#x2019;s own account and not with any present intention of selling or otherwise distributing the Common Stock.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The foregoing requirements, and any assurances given pursuant to such requirements, will
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	be inoperative if (i
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	)&nbsp;the issuance of the shares upon the exercise
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	of a Stock Award
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	or acquisition of Common Stock under the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Stock
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Award has been registered under a then currently effective registration statement
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	under the Securities Act, or (ii
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	)&nbsp;as to any particular requirement, a determination is made by counsel for the Company that such requirement need not be met in the circumstances under the then applicable securities laws.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The Company may, upon advice of counsel to the Company, place legends on stock certificates issued under the Plan as such counsel deems necessary or appropriate in order to comply with applicable securities laws, including, but not limited to, legends restricting the transfer of the Common Stock.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>

<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;;;PADDING:0PT 22PT 0PT 0PT;">
	(g)
</FONT>
<A NAME="SIEN-20151231EX10204A230_HTM__REF147744804">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	the terms of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">

</FONT>

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">

</FONT>

</FONT>

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	a Stock Award

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	or by a combination of such means: (i)&nbsp;causing the Participant to tender a cash payment; (ii)&nbsp;withholding shares of Common Stock from the shares of Common Stock issued or otherwise issuable to the Participant in connection with
</FONT>

</FONT>

	other
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	amount as may be necessary to avoid classification of the Stock Award as a liability for financial accounting purposes); (iii)&nbsp;withholding cash from
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	a Stock Award
</FONT>

<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;;;PADDING:0PT 26PT 0PT 0PT;">
	(i)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	Deferrals.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	To the extent permitted by applicable law, the Board, in its sole discretion, may determine that the delivery of Common Stock or the payment of cash, upon the exercise, vesting or settlement of all or a portion of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	any Stock Award
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">

</FONT>

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Section 409A of the Code
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	(to the extent applicable to a Participant)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Consistent with
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Section 409A of the Code
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	, the Board may provide for distributions while a Participant is still an employee or otherwise providing services to the Company.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The Board is authorized to make deferrals of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Stock
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Awards and determine when, and in what annual percentages, Participants may receive payments, including lump sum payments, following the Participant&#x2019;s termination of Continuous Service, and implement such other terms and conditions consistent with the provisions of the Plan and in accordance with applicable law.

<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;;;PADDING:0PT 26PT 0PT 0PT;">
	(j)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	Compliance with Section 409A.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">

</FONT>

</FONT>

</FONT>

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">

</FONT>

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">

<P STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;;;PADDING:0PT 23PT 0PT 0PT;">
	(k)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	Clawback/Recovery.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	All
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Stock
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Awards granted under the Plan will be subject to recoupment in accordance with any clawback policy that the Company is required to adopt pursuant to the listing standards of any national securities exchange or association on which the Company&#x2019;s securities are listed or as is otherwise required by the Dodd-Frank Wall Street Reform and Consumer Protection Act or other applicable law. In addition, the Board may impose such other clawback, recovery or recoupment provisions in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	a Stock Award
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Agreement as the Board determines necessary or appropriate, including, but not limited to, a reacquisition right in respect of previously acquired shares of Common Stock or other cash or property upon the occurrence of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	an event constituting
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Cause. No recovery of compensation under such a clawback policy will be
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
</FONT>

<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 100%;TEXT-INDENT:36PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">

<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;;;PADDING:0PT 22PT 0PT 0PT;">
	(a)
</FONT>
<A NAME="SIEN-20151231EX10204A230_HTM__REF92447089">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	Capitalization Adjustments
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	In the event of a Capitalization Adjustment, the Board will appropriately and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	proportionately adjust: (i)&nbsp;the class(es) and maximum number of securities subject to th
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	e Plan pursuant to Section&nbsp;3(a) and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	(ii)&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	the class(es) and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	number of securities and price per share of stock subject to outstanding Stock Awards.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The Board will make such adjustments, and its determination will be final, binding and conclusive.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;;;PADDING:0PT 22PT 0PT 0PT;">
	(b)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	Dissolution or Liquidation
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Except as otherwise provided in the Stock Award Agreement, in the event of a dissolution or liquidation of the Company, all outstanding Stock Awards will terminate immediately prior to the completion of such dissolution or liquidation, and the shares of Common Stock subject to the Company&#x2019;s repurchase rights or subject to a forfeiture condition may be repurchased or reacquired by the Company notwithstanding the fact that the holder of such Stock Award
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	is providing Continuous Service;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	provided, however,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	that the Board may, in its sole discretion, cause some or all Stock Awards to become fully vested, exercisable and/or no longer subject to repurchase or forfeiture (to the extent such Stock Awards have not previously expired or terminated) before the dissolution or liquidation is completed but contingent on its completion.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The following provisions will apply to Stock Awards in the event of a Corporate Transaction unless otherwise provided in the instrument evidencing the Stock Award or any other written agreement between the Company or any Affiliate and the Participant or unless otherwise expressly provided by the Board at the time of grant of a Stock Award. In the event of a Corporate Transaction, then, notwithstanding any other provision of the Plan, the Board will take one or more of the following actions with respect to Stock Awards, contingent upon the closing or completion of the Corporate Transaction:

	The Board need not take the same action or actions with respect to all Stock Awards or portions thereof or with respect to all Participants. The Board may take different actions with respect to the vested and unvested portions of a Stock Award.

<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;;;PADDING:0PT 22PT 0PT 0PT;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	A Stock Award may be subject to additional acceleration of vesting and exercisability upon or after a Change in Control as may be provided in the Stock Award Agreement for such Stock Award or as may be provided in any other written agreement between the Company or any Affiliate and the Participant, but in the absence of such provision, no such acceleration will occur.
</FONT>

<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;;;PADDING:0PT 23PT 0PT 0PT;">
	(c)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Capitalization Adjustment
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#x201D; means any change that is made in, or other events that occur with respect to, the Common Stock subject to the Plan or subject to any Stock Award after the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Effective
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Date without the receipt of consideration by the Company through merger, consolidation, reorganization, recapitalization, reincorporation, stock dividend, dividend in property other than cash,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	large nonrecurring cash dividend, stock split,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	reverse stock split,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	liquidating dividend, combination of shares, exchange of shares, change in corporate structure or other similar equity restructuring transaction, as that term is used in Financial Accounting Standards Board Accounting Standards Codification Topic 718 (or any successor thereto)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Notwithstanding the foregoing, the conversion of any convertible securities of the Company will not be treated as a Capitalization Adjustment.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>

	(d)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Cause
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#x201D;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	will have the meaning ascribed to such term in any written agreement between the Participant and the Company
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	or any Affiliate
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	defining such term and, in the absence of such agreement, such term means, with respect to a Participant, the occurrence of any of the following events
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	: (i
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	)&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Participant&#x2019;s willful failure substantially to perform his or her duties and responsibilities to the Company
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	or any Affiliate
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	or deliberate violation of a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	policy of the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Company
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	or any Affiliate
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	; (ii
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	)&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Participant&#x2019;s commission of any act of fraud, embezzlement, dishonesty or any other willful misconduct that has caused or is reasonably expected to result in material injury to the Company
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	or an
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	y
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Affiliate
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	; (iii
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	)&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	unauthorized use or disclosure by Participant of any proprietary information or trade secrets of the Company or any other party to whom the Participant owes an obligation of nondisclosure as a result of his or her relationship with the Company
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	or an
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	y
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Affiliate
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	; or (iv
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	)&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Participant&#x2019;s willful breach of any of his or her obligations under any written agreement or covenant with the Company
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	or an
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	y
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Affiliate
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The determination as to whether a Participant is being terminated for Cause
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	will
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	be made in good faith by the Company and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	will
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	be final and binding on the Participant.

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	outstanding Stock Award
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	s held by such Participant will have no effect upon any determination of the rights or obligations of the Company

	, &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	any Affiliate

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#x201D; means the occurrence, in a single transaction or in a series of related transactions, of any one or more of the following events:

<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<TABLE STYLE="WIDTH:100%;" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0">
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:0PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:0PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 100%;TEXT-INDENT:72PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;;;PADDING:0PT 26PT 0PT 0PT;">
	(i)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	any Exchange Act Person becomes the Owner, directly or indirectly, of securities of the Company representing more than
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	50%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	of the combined voting power of the Company&#x2019;s then outstanding securities other than by virtue of a merger, consolidation or similar transaction.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Notwithstanding the foregoing, a Change in Control will not be deemed to occur (A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	)&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	on account of the acquisition of securities of the Company directly from the Company, (B
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	)&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	on account of the acquisition of securities of the Company by an investor, any affiliate thereof or any other Exchange Act Person that acquires the Company&#x2019;s securities in a transaction or series of related transactions the primary purpose of which is to obtain financing for the Company through the issuance of equity securities
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	, or (
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	C
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	)&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	solely because the level of Ownership held by any Exchange Act Person (the &#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Subject&nbsp;Person
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#x201D;) exceeds the designated percentage threshold of the outstanding voting securities as a result of a repurchase or other acquisition of voting securities by the Company reducing the number of shares outstanding, provided that if a Change in Control would occur (but for the operation of this sentence) as a result of the acquisition of voting securities by the Company, and after such share acquisition, the Subject Person becomes the Owner of any additional voting securities that, assuming the repurchase or other acquisition had not occurred,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

	Notwithstanding the foregoing, a person is treated as a Consultant under this Plan only if a Form S-8 Registration Statement under the Securities Act is available to register either the offer or the sale of the Company&#x2019;s securities to such person.

	Continuous Service
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#x201D; means that the Participant&#x2019;s service with the Company or an Affiliate, whether as an Employee, Director or Consultant, is not interrupted or terminated.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	A change in the capacity in which the Participant renders service to the Company or an Affiliate as an Employee, Consultant or Director or a change in the Entity for which the Participant renders such service, provided that there is no interruption or termination of the Participant&#x2019;s service with the Company or an Affiliate, will not terminate a Participant&#x2019;s Continuous Service
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	For example, a change in status from an Employee of the Company to a Consultant of an Affiliate or to a Director will not constitute an interruption of Continuous Service.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	I
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	f the Entity for which a Participant is rendering services ceases to qualify as an Affiliate, as determined by the Board in its sole discretion, such Participant&#x2019;s Continuous Service will be considered to have terminated on the date such Entity ceases to qualify as an Affiliate.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	To the extent permitted by law, the Board or the chief executive officer of the Company, in that party&#x2019;s sole discretion, may determine whether Continuous Service will be considered interrupted in the case of (i
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	)&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	any leave of absence approved by the Board or chief executive officer, including sick leave, military leave or any other personal leave, or (ii
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	)&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	transfers between the Company, an Affiliate, or their successors.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	In addition, if required for exemption from or compliance with
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Section 409A of the Code
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	, the determination of whether there has been a termination of Continuous Service will be made, and such term will be construed, in a manner that is consistent with the definition of &#x201C;separation from service&#x201D; as defined under Treasury Regulation Section 1.409A-1(h).
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	leave of absence will be treated as Continuous Serv
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	ice for purposes of vesting in a Stock
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Award only to such extent as may be provided in the Company&#x2019;s leave of absence policy, in the written terms of any leave of absence agreement or policy applicable to the Participant, or as otherwise required by law.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">

<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;;;PADDING:0PT 26PT 0PT 0PT;">
	(l)

<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;;;PADDING:0PT 20PT 0PT 0PT;">

<P STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;;;PADDING:0PT 22PT 0PT 0PT;">
	(n)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Disability
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#x201D; means, with respect to a Participant, the inability of such Participant to engage in any substantial gainful activity by reason of any medically determinable physical or mental impairment that can be expected to result in death or that has lasted or can be expected to last for a continuous period of not less than 12&nbsp;months as provided in Se
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	ctions&nbsp;22(e)(3) and 409A(a)(2)(C
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	)(i) of the Code, and will be determined by the Board on the basis of such medical evidence as the Board deems warranted under the circumstances.

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>

</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 100%;TEXT-INDENT:36PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;;;PADDING:0PT 23PT 0PT 0PT;">
	(s)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Exchange Act Person
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#x201D;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	means any natural person, Entity or &#x201C;group&#x201D; (within the meaning of Section&nbsp;13(d) or 14(d) of the Exchange Act), except that &#x201C;Exchange&nbsp;Act&nbsp;Person&#x201D; will not include (i)&nbsp;the Company or any Subsidiary of the Company, (ii)&nbsp;any employee benefit plan of the Company or any Subsidiary of the Company or any trustee or other fiduciary holding securities under an employee benefit plan of the Company or any Subsidiary of the Company, (iii)&nbsp;an underwriter temporarily holding securities pursuant to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	a registered public
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	offering of such securities, (iv)&nbsp;an Entity Owned, directly or indirectly, by the stockholders of the Company in substantially the same proportions as their Ow
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	nership of stock of the Company,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	or (v)&nbsp;any natural person, Entity or &#x201C;group&#x201D; (within the meaning of Section&nbsp;13(d) or 14(d) of the Exchange Act) that, as of the Effective Date, is the Owner, directly or indirectly, of securities of the Company representing more than
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	50%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	of the combined voting power of the Company&#x2019;s then outstanding securities.
</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 24PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	Stock Option Grant Notice
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Sientra, Inc. (the &#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Company
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201D;), pursuant to its Inducement Plan (the &#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Plan
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201D;), hereby grants to Optionholder an option to purchase the number of shares of the Company&#x2019;s Common Stock set forth below.&nbsp;&nbsp;This option is subject to all of the terms and conditions as set forth in this notice, in the Option Agreement, the Plan and the Notice of Exercise, all of which are attached hereto and incorporated herein in their entirety.&nbsp;&nbsp;Capitalized terms not explicitly defined herein but defined in the Plan or the Option Agreement will have the same definitions as in the Plan or the Option Agreement. If there is any conflict between the terms in this notice and the Plan, the terms of the Plan will control.
</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">

	&nbsp;

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 24PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 14PT;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
